    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-18T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="45"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d45">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.0146/798: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Tsingtao</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Meyer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tsingtao</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-18T14:00:00+09:00"
                            >June 18, 1940—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 18—12:31 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>82. Shanghai’s June 16, 4 p.m.<note n="63" xml:id="d45fn63">Not printed.</note>
                    In reply to Department’s 258, March [<hi rend="italic">June</hi>] 13, 6 p.m.,
                    concerning Tokyo’s 438, June 11, 10 p.m., and Shanghai’s 527, June 15, 3
                        p.m.,<note n="64" xml:id="d45fn64">Telegrams No. 258 and No. 527 not
                        printed.</note> Admiral Hart comments as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“All European commanders belligerent forces Shanghai, Tientsin, Peiping,
                            including Italians, are loyally carrying out their agreements maintain
                            peaceful <hi rend="italic">statics quo</hi> and working arrangements are
                            complete. American Admiral was in fact the Senior Officer but acted
                            primarily in behalf of naval, military representative of a power
                            entirely unengaged in hostilities. Japanese Admiral was so informed
                            immediately on completion informal conversations which resulted in the
                            agreements.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated to Shanghai, Tokyo, Peiping, and Chungking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Meyer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
